            },
            "notes": "Saukko, this isn't a bug - it's a feature. Native menu & screen size is 640x480 ... how do you scale an 'image' from 640x480 (ratio 1.3) to fit into a size of 1980x1024 (ratio 1.6)?",
            "created_on": "2013-12-08T07:52:00Z",
            "details": []
        },
        {
            "id": 2338,
            "user": {
                "id": 90,
                "name": "Saukko"
            },
            "notes": "If this is a feature, it's a bthering feature then. I liked it more that it fills the whole screen like in the original ET.\r\nSo I guess this isn't possible to be changed?\r\n\r\n-*S",
            "created_on": "2013-12-08T11:07:15Z",
            "details": []
        },
        {
            "id": 2342,
            "user": {
                "id": 140,
                "name": "Spyhawk"
            },
            "notes": "The actual situation isn't optimal, but it's way better than having a distorted screen.\r\n\r\nWhat could be done:\r\n\r\n* file the black areas with some dummy images, or\r\n* recreate many widescreen images from scratch, and use the correct one depending on the aspect ratio.\r\n\r\nThe second option is obviously more difficult, and requires to rethink the whole organization of the screen images + code.",
            "created_on": "2013-12-08T11:56:21Z",
            "details": []
        },
        {
            "id": 2351,
            "user": {
                "id": 90,
                "name": "Saukko"
            },
            "notes": "My suggestion would be to fill these black spots in limbomenu with a similar greenish colour that it already has. This would be the easiest way. Or if it's possible to use the vanila ET's settings in these cases. But there's no denying that those black spots look rather horrific. ;)\r\n\r\nMy artistic skills wouldn't be nowhere near to accomplish anything of these possible solutions, maybe someone with the determination and skills would be able to make this happen.\r\n\r\n-*S",
